The '''[[Dominican Republic]]''' is a signatory to the [[Berne Convention]], and the basic law on [[copyright]] is contained in ''Law No. 65-00 on Copyright of August 21, 2000'' as supplemented by the ''Regulations of Application of the Law No. 65-00 on Copyright, as enacted on March 14, 2001''.<ref>[http://portal.unesco.org/culture/en/ev.php-URL_ID=15395&URL_DO=DO_TOPIC&URL_SECTION=201.html Dominican Republic.] [[UNESCO]], 2013. Retrieved 8 July 2013.</ref>

