{{Infobox football biography | name = Fahad Alenazi | image = | fullname = Fahad Saleh Alenazi | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1988|9|1|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Kuwait City]], [[Kuwait]] | height = 1.75 m | position = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]] | currentclub = [[Kuwait SC]] | clubnumber = 7 | youthyears1 = 2008–2009 | youthclubs1 = [[Kazma Sporting Club|Kazma]] | years1 = 2009–2011 | clubs1 = [[Kazma Sporting Club|Kazma]] | caps1 = 19 | goals1 = 9 | years2 = 2010 | clubs2 = → [[FK Partizan|Partizan B]] (loan) | caps2 = 1 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2011–2012 | clubs3 = → [[Ittihad FC]] (loan) | caps3 = 7 | goals3 = 2<ref>{{cite news |title=فهد العنزي - كرة القدم - Eurosport Arabia|url=http://eurosport.anayou.com/football/%D9%81%D9%87%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%86%D8%B2%D9%8A_prs227927/ar-person.shtml|date=9 September 2011 |accessdate=9 September 2011 }}</ref> | years4 = 2012– | clubs4 = [[Kuwait SC]] | caps4 = 145 | goals4 = 28 | clubs5 = [[Al-Markhiya Sports Club|Al-Markhiya]] (loan) | years5 = 2018– | caps5=3 |goals5=1 | nationalyears1 = 2009– | nationalteam1 = [[Kuwait national football team|Kuwait]] | nationalcaps1 = 49 | nationalgoals1 = 4 | ntupdate = 14 January 2018 | pcupdate = 28 December 2017 }}
'''Fahad Alenazi''' ({{lang-ar|فهد العنزي}}, born 1 September 1988) is a [[Kuwait]]i Professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for the [[Kuwaiti Premier League]] club [[Kuwait SC]].<ref name="NFT">{{NFT player|id=30652|name=Fahad Al-Enezi|accessdate=28 October 2010}}</ref>
==Career== ===FK Partizan=== On October 25 of 2010, Fahad obtained permission from the [[Kazma Sporting Club|Kazma]] board for a week-long vacation to travel to [[Saudi Arabia]].<ref>{{cite news|title=العنزي يخضع للتجربة في صربيا |url=http://www.aljarida.com/aljarida/Article.aspx?id=181571 |work=Al Jarida |date=25 October 2010 |accessdate=28 October 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101106071928/http://aljarida.com/aljarida/Article.aspx?id=181571 |archivedate=6 November 2010 |df= }}</ref> However, Fahad did not travel to [[Saudi Arabia]]; he traveled to [[Serbia]] to get a trial with [[FK Partizan]] for a week so that they may sign him in the January transfer window.<ref>{{cite news |title=Alenazi na probi u Partizanu|url=http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/sport.72.html:305885-Alenazi-na-probi-u-Partizanu|work=[[Večernje novosti]]|date=31 October 2010 |accessdate=31 October 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Reprezentativac Kuvajta u Humskoj (VIDEO) |url=http://www.sportal.rs/news.php?id=38507 |work=sportal.rs |date=31 October 2010 |accessdate=31 October 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101102170320/http://sportal.rs/news.php?id=38507 |archivedate=2 November 2010 |df= }}</ref> He played one game for Partizan B team in the Serbian Reserves First League,<ref>[http://www.b92.net/sport/fudbal/vesti.php?yyyy=2010&mm=11&dd=05&nav_id=470319 Partizan “B” savladao BASK] at [[B92]], 5-11-2010, retrieved 30-11-2014 {{sr icon}}</ref> and Fahad returned to Kuwait.
===Itthiad FC=== In the 2011 season Fahad joined Ittihad FC on loan from Kazma.His spell at Ittihad FC was short and without success due to injuries and financial problems with the club.
==Style of play== Al Enezi is a pacy customer who tends to cause problems for defending opposition on the left wing with his combination of skill, determination and sheer speed. He is renowned for his trait of running box-to-box and the ability to slot-in dangerous shots and crosses from outside the thirty-yard box. In light of his developing career, Al Enezi has come to be recognised, questionably, as the 'fastest player in Kuwait football'.
